						               													<description>2-4 player bluffing and dice rolling card game set in a science-fiction universe.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player starts the game with three Eye of Truth cards and ten hero cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Heroes have stats (strength, courage, wisdom, honor, and temper) on the back and stats (attack, defense) on the front. Heroes also have abilities ok the front. Players may never look at the backs of their cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The attacking player calls out one of the stats from the back of the cards, which could be truth or a lie. The defending player(s) call out the attacker's value for that same stat, which could be true or a lie. The attacking player announces the attack value on his/her card. The defending player(s) also do this regarding the defense value of their card. Finally, each player rolls a die and adds these three values (their die roll, the value they called out from the front, and the value that was called out to them from the back) and the highest value takes the trick and collects all cards played.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a player believes that a called was false, they may play an Eye of Truth card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a player ever runs out of Eye of Truth cards or hero cards, they are out of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
